{:synth/id   :lorenz-fm
 :synth/tags [:chaos :lorenz :fm :hybrid :arc-ready]
 :synth/doc  "FM synthesis with Lorenz chaos modulation — hybrid physical/spectral voice.

  A SinOsc carrier frequency-modulated by the output of a Lorenz oscillator.
  When the Lorenz system is stable (low :chaos), the modulation is nearly zero
  and the carrier is a clean sine. As :chaos increases, the Lorenz trajectory
  widens and the FM modulation index grows — the carrier becomes increasingly
  unstable, producing sidebands at chaotic (inharmonic) intervals.

  At high :chaos the modulation depth is large enough that the carrier frequency
  deviates by hundreds of Hz per sample — the result is a dense FM spectrum with
  no fixed relationship between partials. The combination of FM (harmonic by
  nature) with chaotic modulation (inharmonic) produces a sound impossible with
  standard FM synthesis.

  Signal flow:
    Lorenz(s, r(chaos), b, h) → x+y+z mix / 30 → scale by fm-depth
    SinOsc(freq + chaos_mod * freq) → RLPF → Pan2 → Out

  :chaos [0..1] controls Lorenz r: 10 + 40 × chaos (see :chaos-lorenz for
  the r-to-behavior mapping).

  :fm-depth controls how much the normalized Lorenz output modulates frequency.
  At fm-depth=0.5 the modulation can shift the carrier by ±0.5× :freq, which
  at 440 Hz means ±220 Hz deviation per Lorenz value. At deep chaos (r=50) the
  Lorenz output swings widely, producing dramatic pitch smearing.

  Recommended starting point:
    (sc/sc-play! {:synth :lorenz-fm :freq 220 :amp 0.5 :chaos 0.2 :fm-depth 0.3})
  Then sweep :chaos via apply-trajectory! for a controlled destabilization.

  A second slower Lorenz (at :s 12, different initial conditions) modulates the
  filter cutoff — this adds a second layer of correlated chaos that makes the
  timbre change track the pitch change loosely."
 :args  {:freq      440.0
         :freq-cut  2400.0
         :freq-res  0.5
         :chaos     0.3
         :fm-depth  0.4
         :s         10.0
         :b         2.667
         :h         0.05
         :amp       0.45
         :attack    0.05
         :release   3.0
         :pan       0.0}
 :graph [:out 0
          [:pan2
           [:* [:env-gen [:asr :attack 1.0 :release] :gate :amp]
               [:rlpf
                [:sin-osc
                 [:+ :freq
                  [:* :freq
                   [:* :fm-depth
                    [:* [:/ 1.0 30.0]
                     [:mix [[:lorenz :s [:+ 10.0 [:* 40.0 :chaos]] :b :h]]]]]]]]
                :freq-cut
                :freq-res]]
           :pan]]}
